#ANDROID

*OS: Ubuntu 14.10

1. Install Node.js:
> $ sudo apt-get install nodejs
2. Install latest Cordova and Ionic command-line tools:
> $ npm install -g cordova ionic
3. Create an Ionic project:
> $ ionic start janssen blank
4. Copy www/ folder into janssen/www/
5. Build app:
> $ cd janssen
> $ ionic platform add android
> $ ionic build android
6. Start Android project from janssen/platform/android
   
#IOS

*OS: MacOS

1. Install Node.js:
> $ sudo apt-get install nodejs
2. Install latest Cordova and Ionic command-line tools:
> $ npm install -g cordova ionic
3. Create an Ionic project:
> $ ionic start janssen blank
4. Copy www/ folder into janssen/www/
5. Build app:
> $ cd janssen
> $ ionic platform add ios
> $ ionic build ios
6. Start Xcode project from janssen/platform/ios/

#WINDOWS PHONE 8

*OS: Windows 8.1

1. Install Visual Studio 2013 Community
2. Run Visual Studio. File->New->Project. Templates->Visual C#->Store Apps->Windows Phone Apps, select template "HTML 5 App (Windows Phone Silverlight)"
3. Copy www/ folder into Html/ in Solution Explorer.
4. Build solution.

#WINDOWS PHONE 7

*OS: Windows 7

1. Install Visual Studio Express 2010 
2. Downolad Cordova developer tools from the PhoneGap Web site
3. Run Visual Studio. File->New->Project. Visual C#->Silverlight for Windows Phone, select template "Cordova-x.x.x-Starter"
4. Copy www/ folder into Html/ in Solution Explorer.
5. Build solution.